118
00:09:48,601 --> 00:09:54,801
And you can even have some goodies, but you don't get addicted to satisfying all your desires.

119
00:09:53,640 --> 00:10:00,640
You cut off your superfluous and unnecessary desires, except maybe for cherry jam.

120
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:07,841
I mean, it's a kind of nice, I mean, it sounds sort of inconsistent, but it's just a kind of flexible, sensible view.

121
00:10:07,841 --> 00:10:16,560
I mean, you don't have to cut off all your unnecessary desires, but only if you don't, but you can't let them get enslave you.

122
00:10:16,561 --> 00:10:21,041
If you become addicted to smoking, for instance, then you've gone too far.

123
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:24,000
And if you became addicted to cherry jam, that wouldn't be good either.

124
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:30,960
But if you can enjoy them, this is all talked about on 360 at the about 20 lines from the bottom.

125
00:10:30,961 --> 00:10:33,040
For how can a man shake off his habits?

126
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:39,201
What can become of him if he's in bondage to the habit of satisfying the innumerable desires he's created for himself?

127
00:10:39,201 --> 00:10:44,721
And then below that, next paragraph, the monastic way is very different.

128
00:10:44,721 --> 00:10:47,201
Obedient, fasting, and prayer are laughed at.

129
00:10:47,201 --> 00:10:50,241
Yet only through them lies the way to real true freedom.

130
00:10:50,241 --> 00:10:54,400
I cut off my superfluous and unnecessary desires.

131
00:10:54,721 --> 00:11:04,561
So a little skipping to the bottom, which is most capable, see, who's most capable of conceiving a great idea and serving it?

132
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:10,801
The rich man in his isolation, or the man who has freed himself from the tyranny of material things and habits.

133
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:14,161
So that's a sensible view.

134
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:16,400
