00:36:52,681 --> 00:36:57,800
And so now we're going to expect a complicated sort of answer.

424
00:36:57,800 --> 00:37:01,081
Or maybe you're not expecting it, but you're going to get a complicated answer.

425
00:37:01,081 --> 00:37:11,000
Because this is the first place, and one of the only places, I think, where Dostoevsky diverges from the Russian Orthodox Church.

426
00:37:11,001 --> 00:37:16,280
I mean, remember, the Russian Orthodox Church is the answer to the antinomies.

427
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:24,921
And so it ought to come out that somehow the relation of what he says to the Russian Orthodox Church ought to be pretty similar.

428
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:27,560
But on confession, he just thinks the church is wrong.

429
00:37:27,561 --> 00:37:35,561
And after all, he's got his own brilliant view about all of these existentialized notions.

430
00:37:35,561 --> 00:37:44,680
And when he existentializes confession, which is what he's about to do, he has his ideas about what it really is when it isn't magical.

431
00:37:44,681 --> 00:37:52,840
And he thinks just somebody going and confessing to somebody else who has the power to absolve them and says you're forgiven, that that's magic.

432
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:54,800
And we're not going to have that kind of magic.

433
00:37:54,521 --> 00:37:57,920
So out with the Russian Orthodox view of confession.

434
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:16,561
Because even for the Russian Orthodox, as for the Catholic, the Roman Catholics, confession is private and secret between the person and the sinner, you or me, and the person they're confessing to, the priest.

435
00:38:16,561 --> 00:38:22,001
And moreover, it's secret so that nobody needs to know what you confess.

436
00:38:22,001 --> 00:38:27,280
That's all just wrong, psychologically or existentially, let's say, spiritually.

437
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:28,400
So we have to go on.

438
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:30,081
So get rid of that.

439
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:34,321
So the question is, what should the Russian Orthodox Church do?

440
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:38,481
Well, that's the second stage would be to look at Zosima.

441
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:42,721
Because normally, Zosima gets it right.

442
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:51,920
Again, not always, but in this case, what Zosima does is obviously what confession should be.

443
00:38:54,161 --> 00:38:55,681
But you don't have to believe me.

